<i>Previously on "Imposters"...</i>

00:18.869 --> 00:19.943
<i>My name is Molly,</i>

00:20.036 --> 00:23.104
<i>and I'm looking for a happy,
normal life.</i>

00:23.106 --> 00:24.972
I'm Shelly. Shelly Cohen. I'm...

00:24.974 --> 00:26.374
fairly confident you know my ex-wife.

00:26.376 --> 00:27.608
[gasps]

00:30.313 --> 00:31.879
I think I want to go to the Harbor.

00:31.881 --> 00:33.815
<i>Your time here will be dedicated</i>

00:33.817 --> 00:36.117
to the idea of wholeness.

00:36.119 --> 00:37.952
Group sessions take place once a day.

00:37.954 --> 00:40.154
Oh! Oh, my God, I'm so sorry.

00:40.156 --> 00:42.223
I think you forgot to
give me back my money.

00:42.225 --> 00:43.358
I don't like you so much.

00:43.360 --> 00:45.460
We can do a job together,

00:45.462 --> 00:47.595
see if we... fit.

00:47.597 --> 00:48.730
<i>This work can mess with your head</i>

00:48.732 --> 00:49.731
and your heart.

00:49.733 --> 00:50.732
Be careful.

00:50.734 --> 00:51.733
Saffron Keyes,

00:51.735 --> 00:52.734
will you marry me?

00:52.736 --> 00:53.968
<i>Maddie Jonson.</i>

00:53.970 --> 00:55.636
<i>Who are you now?</i>

00:55.638 --> 00:58.639
This office is for agents
who didn't screw the pooch.

00:58.641 --> 00:59.874
Ready to go?

00:59.876 --> 01:01.642
Anybody need a ride?

01:01.644 --> 01:03.411
- Maxie.
- Chin up, Max.

01:03.413 --> 01:04.779
It's better to be sad than dead.

01:04.781 --> 01:07.348
Just, no more lying to each other, okay?

01:07.350 --> 01:08.516
So I guess we need a new code.

01:08.518 --> 01:09.751
No lying about money.

01:09.753 --> 01:11.686
<i>I just sold an actual boat.</i>

01:11.688 --> 01:13.020
<i>No lying about drinking.</i>

01:13.022 --> 01:15.523
- No lying about sex.
- Okay.

01:15.525 --> 01:17.358
Looks like you broke
through that writer's block.

01:17.360 --> 01:18.359
So what's the story?

01:18.361 --> 01:19.594
It's based on my, uh...

01:19.596 --> 01:21.662
my cousin, Callie Shuman.

01:21.664 --> 01:22.930
It's fiction.

01:22.932 --> 01:24.432
[gun clicks]

01:24.434 --> 01:25.800
Do me a favor and get it over with.

01:25.802 --> 01:27.001
I'm not gonna kill you.

01:27.003 --> 01:28.836
At least not just yet.

01:32.375 --> 01:34.942
[monitor beeping]

01:34.944 --> 01:36.310
[groans]

01:37.547 --> 01:38.646
Ouch.

01:38.648 --> 01:40.681
Oh, you're awake.

01:40.683 --> 01:43.551
Beginning to wonder if they
put me in with a vegetable.

01:43.553 --> 01:45.653
[chuckles]

01:45.655 --> 01:46.788
And who might you be?

01:46.790 --> 01:49.223
Louie. Jenkins.

01:49.225 --> 01:50.525
Shelly Cohen.

01:52.162 --> 01:53.361
[exhales heavily]

01:57.467 --> 02:00.001
Uh-huh. Hello to you, sir.

02:00.003 --> 02:01.002
All right.

02:01.004 --> 02:03.805
[handcuffs clinking]

02:05.074 --> 02:06.874
[sighs] Well, that's a surprise.

02:06.876 --> 02:10.544
You must be...

02:10.547 --> 02:12.046
someone important.

02:13.583 --> 02:15.750
I must be.

02:15.752 --> 02:17.385
Don't need these.

02:19.923 --> 02:21.656
[lock clicks]

02:22.826 --> 02:24.492
Open.

02:25.428 --> 02:27.595
Now, Louie,

02:27.597 --> 02:31.432
what brings you to our lovely
little semi-private suite?

02:31.434 --> 02:33.000
I-I had surgery.

02:33.002 --> 02:34.035
Mm.

02:34.037 --> 02:35.903
You had surgery, indeed.

02:35.905 --> 02:38.973
You had your third
exploratory splenectomy.

02:38.975 --> 02:40.341
Say that three times fast.

02:40.343 --> 02:42.176
My surgeon strongly advised...

02:42.178 --> 02:44.879
"Your surgeon strongly advised."

02:44.881 --> 02:47.215
Piece of advice, Louie.

02:47.217 --> 02:48.583
[clears throat]

02:48.585 --> 02:51.319
Don't trust a person whose only job

02:51.321 --> 02:54.455
is to slice open your guts.

02:54.457 --> 02:55.857
Right?

02:57.026 --> 02:59.227
Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

02:59.229 --> 03:00.461
[whispers] No.

03:00.463 --> 03:02.063
See you in a minute.

03:02.065 --> 03:03.865
I got a question for you, Louie.

03:03.867 --> 03:06.300
Did you really have surgery
because you needed it,

03:06.302 --> 03:08.769
or is it possible that this way,

03:08.771 --> 03:11.639
you were guaranteed to get some
attention from your family?

03:11.641 --> 03:13.374
Do you think, maybe,

03:13.376 --> 03:16.878
it was a way for...

03:16.880 --> 03:20.915
Daniel and Sarah and
Lisa and Daniel Junior

03:20.917 --> 03:24.085
to give you some
much-needed attention, Louie?

03:25.688 --> 03:28.155
You must think

03:28.157 --> 03:30.625
I'm horrible.

03:30.627 --> 03:31.893
Come on, Louie.

03:31.895 --> 03:33.394
You haven't heard a word I've said.

03:33.396 --> 03:35.763
I think you...

03:35.765 --> 03:37.632
[inhales sharply]

03:37.634 --> 03:39.233
...are a Grade A,

03:39.235 --> 03:42.270
capital B badass.

03:42.272 --> 03:43.671
Yeah?

03:43.673 --> 03:45.006
Oh, yeah, man.

03:45.008 --> 03:46.407
You're not leaving, are you?

03:46.409 --> 03:49.610
Oh, well, I'm uninsured. [clicks tongue]

03:49.612 --> 03:51.646
But there's a policeman out there.

03:51.648 --> 03:53.614
Yes, I figured there might be,

03:53.616 --> 03:55.683
and I was wondering if you could give me

03:55.685 --> 03:57.952
just a teeny tiny little
bit of help with that?

04:00.353 --> 04:02.189
Excuse me, officer.

04:02.191 --> 04:05.459
This young man says he'd
like to speak with you.

04:05.461 --> 04:08.429
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:08.431 --> 04:15.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:15.471 --> 04:17.438
I told you everything, Sal.

04:17.440 --> 04:18.873
I want to hear it again.

04:18.875 --> 04:22.777
- Do you work for the FBI?
- No.

04:22.779 --> 04:25.279
Why didn't you tell the Doctor
the truth about Patrick?

04:25.281 --> 04:26.314
Because I thought I could handle it,

04:26.316 --> 04:27.515
that I could fix it.

04:27.517 --> 04:29.083
How much is the ring worth?

04:29.085 --> 04:30.318
$1.3 million.

04:30.320 --> 04:31.786
And who has the ring now?

04:31.788 --> 04:33.387
I don't know.

04:33.389 --> 04:35.222
And where are Ezra, Richard, and Jules?

04:35.224 --> 04:37.191
I told you, I don't know.

04:37.193 --> 04:39.527
- Are they with Maddie?
- I don't know.

04:39.529 --> 04:41.662
Were they working together
to double-cross the Doctor?

04:41.664 --> 04:43.731
All I know is the original plan.

04:43.733 --> 04:45.132
For you to impersonate the Doctor?

04:45.134 --> 04:46.968
I only did that to bait the FBI.

04:46.970 --> 04:48.536
<i>It was the only way to get their money,</i>

04:48.538 --> 04:50.338
<i>and I was gonna give it to the Doctor.</i>

04:50.340 --> 04:51.405
<i>Every dime.</i>

04:51.407 --> 04:52.740
<i>But Maddie screwed me.</i>

04:52.742 --> 04:54.675
Why do you think she did that?

04:57.914 --> 05:00.715
Max?

05:00.717 --> 05:03.651
Why do you think she did that?

05:03.653 --> 05:06.687
Maybe she was just trying
to watch out for herself.

05:06.689 --> 05:09.123
Or maybe she just forgot
who her real friends are.

05:11.160 --> 05:12.693
What did they do to you?

05:14.263 --> 05:17.331
[phone buzzing]

05:22.505 --> 05:24.405
Yes, Doctor?

05:24.407 --> 05:25.439
I understand.

05:28.511 --> 05:30.878
Does this mean the Doctor
is giving me another chance,

05:30.880 --> 05:33.781
or are you just gonna
kill me somewhere else?

05:33.783 --> 05:35.383
I guess we'll see.

05:35.385 --> 05:37.785
You're driving.

05:37.787 --> 05:39.587
Where to?

05:39.589 --> 05:40.855
Wherever the hell I tell you.

05:40.857 --> 05:42.890
[engine turns over]

05:47.730 --> 05:50.731
<i>[gentle acoustic guitar]</i>

05:50.733 --> 05:57.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:03.746 --> 06:05.880
[rooster crows]

06:05.882 --> 06:07.648
<i>Hola, guapa.</i>

06:07.650 --> 06:08.783
Hi, Jules.

06:08.785 --> 06:11.318
I'm so glad to see you.

06:11.320 --> 06:13.120
- I was worried you'd get lost.
- Me too.

06:13.122 --> 06:15.289
- It's so beautiful here.
- [laughs] Yes.

06:15.965 --> 06:16.791
I have the pictures.

06:16.793 --> 06:19.060
- Great. Want to come inside?
- Yeah.

06:20.263 --> 06:22.596
What is all this?

06:22.598 --> 06:24.999
People call it an arts commune,

06:25.001 --> 06:27.001
but we just call it the Neighborhood.

06:27.003 --> 06:31.972
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:31.974 --> 06:33.774
What a magical place.

06:33.776 --> 06:35.409
No, it's not magic.

06:35.411 --> 06:37.778
It's very human, you know?

06:38.176 --> 06:39.180
Here.

06:39.182 --> 06:41.082
Let's go meet our guide.

06:41.084 --> 06:43.818
