14:08.369 --> 14:09.568
Honestly, Jules,

14:09.570 --> 14:13.005
I try to understand,

14:13.007 --> 14:14.640
but you got everything you wanted.

14:14.642 --> 14:18.477
What I wanted was to be an artist.

14:18.479 --> 14:20.112
Now I'm a worthless piece of shit.

14:20.114 --> 14:21.547
What you did in the grand scheme

14:21.549 --> 14:23.649
is nothing.

14:23.651 --> 14:25.884
Besides, no one will ever find out,

14:25.886 --> 14:28.053
because it's fixed.

14:28.055 --> 14:30.322
That's what power and influence does.

14:30.324 --> 14:32.658
It fixes things.

14:32.660 --> 14:34.827
You need to accept that.

14:34.829 --> 14:37.162
- Yeah, no.
- Poor Jules.

14:37.164 --> 14:39.464
Jules likes to suffer.

14:39.466 --> 14:42.634
Jules mistakes suffering
for authenticity.

14:44.238 --> 14:46.905
Besides,

14:46.907 --> 14:48.740
every family needs a...

14:50.277 --> 14:51.977
Lucky for you,

14:51.979 --> 14:54.746
we will always be there to rescue you.

14:54.748 --> 15:01.787
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:19.440 --> 15:21.139
[gasps]

15:22.610 --> 15:25.444
[groans]

15:28.716 --> 15:31.350
[retches]

15:33.287 --> 15:36.555
[laughter and chatter]

15:36.557 --> 15:38.657
<i>Hola.</i>

15:38.659 --> 15:40.792
<i>- Buenos días.
- Buenos días.</i>

15:40.794 --> 15:43.061
[speaking Spanish]

15:43.063 --> 15:46.064
<i>[light pop music]</i>

15:46.066 --> 15:47.199
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:47.201 --> 15:48.967
Gracias.

15:48.969 --> 15:56.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:57.311 --> 15:58.644
It's true.

15:58.646 --> 15:59.978
I can't sing, and I can't dance.

15:59.980 --> 16:02.981
But you said you'd entertain me.

16:02.983 --> 16:04.650
Come on, there must be something.

16:04.652 --> 16:07.085
Yeah, okay, there's, like,
one stupid impression.

16:07.087 --> 16:09.221
Okay, do it.

16:09.223 --> 16:11.323
Oh, okay. Um...

16:11.325 --> 16:13.492
[clears throat]

16:13.494 --> 16:15.093
[laughs]

16:15.095 --> 16:17.362
[British accent] I'm, uh...

16:17.364 --> 16:19.731
I'm, uh... I'm just a boy,

16:19.733 --> 16:22.000
standing in front of a girl,

16:22.002 --> 16:24.503
asking her to love him.

16:26.040 --> 16:27.372
What is that?

16:27.374 --> 16:28.874
That's Hugh Grant.

16:28.876 --> 16:30.575
- That's dead-on.
- Who's Hugh Grant?

16:30.577 --> 16:32.177
Who's Hugh Grant? Seriously?

16:32.179 --> 16:35.380
- I have no idea.
- He's in all those rom-coms.

16:35.382 --> 16:37.115
Rom-com, like romantic comedies?

16:37.117 --> 16:38.684
What's that face for?

16:38.686 --> 16:40.419
- You like those movies?
- Oh, my God, yes.

16:40.421 --> 16:41.753
And hello, everyone does.

16:41.755 --> 16:43.188
Okay.

16:43.190 --> 16:44.289
Two people fall instantly in love,

16:44.291 --> 16:45.624
but surprise,

16:45.626 --> 16:47.526
something really dumb keeps them apart,

16:47.528 --> 16:48.961
like a mis... [laughs]

16:48.963 --> 16:50.028
- Like a mis...
- "Mis" what?

16:50.030 --> 16:51.530
- M-m-mistake?
- Ah!

16:51.532 --> 16:53.365
- Mistletoe?
- Mis... ah, I can't remember.

16:53.367 --> 16:54.633
I had too much champagne.

16:54.635 --> 16:55.934
- Misunderstanding?
- Exactly.

16:55.936 --> 16:57.241
- Yeah.
- Of course,

16:57.276 --> 16:59.873
they find each other again and
it ends happily after ever.

16:59.908 --> 17:00.906
- Ever after.
- Whatever.

17:00.908 --> 17:02.541
And you know,
that's why people watch those movies,

17:02.543 --> 17:03.675
'cause they want to
believe it's possible.

17:03.677 --> 17:05.577
And you believe it's possible?

17:08.582 --> 17:09.982
I see.

17:09.983 --> 17:11.750
There is a sad story in there.

17:13.287 --> 17:14.953
Well, what about you?

17:14.954 --> 17:18.190
I mean, you haven't told
me anything about yourself.

17:21.328 --> 17:23.795
Who cares about the past?

17:23.797 --> 17:25.964
All that I want is to
be happy right now.

17:28.068 --> 17:32.738
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:37.838 --> 17:39.773
I'd like to talk to
you about your sister.

17:39.775 --> 17:40.907
My sister?

17:40.909 --> 17:43.043
You mentioned her last night

17:43.045 --> 17:44.411
in Brian's group.

17:44.413 --> 17:46.279
He said you blurted something out.

17:46.281 --> 17:48.181
You told me you were the only child

17:48.183 --> 17:49.649
of a single mother.

17:49.651 --> 17:51.918
Mm-hmm. Yeah, I do that all the time.

17:51.920 --> 17:54.554
You know,
it's just because we're so distant,

17:54.556 --> 17:57.057
it just feels like I'm an
only child at this point.

17:57.059 --> 18:00.160
What prompted you to mention
your sister in group?

18:00.162 --> 18:03.296
Well, Linda was saying
something about her brother...

18:03.298 --> 18:04.998
Molly, do you have a sister?

18:05.000 --> 18:07.400
[laughs] Excuse me?

18:07.402 --> 18:10.336
Do you have a sister?

18:10.338 --> 18:13.273
I'm not really sure why you're
asking me that question.

18:13.275 --> 18:15.008
If you don't have a sister,
that means that it was

18:15.010 --> 18:18.244
more important for you
to make Linda feel better

18:18.246 --> 18:19.579
than to tell the truth.

18:19.581 --> 18:21.848
Jesus, I was just trying to help, man.

18:21.850 --> 18:23.450
How?

18:23.452 --> 18:25.819
How were you trying to help Linda?

18:25.821 --> 18:27.921
I don't know. Why don't you tell me?

18:27.923 --> 18:29.456
You lied to Linda,

18:29.458 --> 18:31.658
just like you're lying to me right now.

18:31.660 --> 18:34.461
Why come to a place like
this to make things up?

18:34.463 --> 18:37.964
Why sit here with me and lie?

18:37.966 --> 18:40.033
So that's it? You think you know me?

18:40.035 --> 18:42.769
You've got me figured out after,
what, three sessions?

18:42.771 --> 18:45.605
Hardly. I just wonder
how well you know yourself.

18:48.009 --> 18:50.076
We talk a lot here about the false self

18:50.078 --> 18:51.311
versus the authentic self.

18:51.313 --> 18:52.378
Mm-hmm.

18:52.380 --> 18:54.647
And some people find it...

18:54.649 --> 18:58.885
safer or easier or
even more advantageous

18:58.887 --> 19:02.355
to go through life projecting
a counterfeit image

19:02.357 --> 19:04.557
as a way to hide who they really are.

19:04.559 --> 19:08.528
Oh, so you... you're saying I'm hiding?

19:08.530 --> 19:10.897
No, I think you figured out
a long time ago

19:10.899 --> 19:13.700
that if you could read
someone in just the right way,

19:13.702 --> 19:17.137
then you can give them
exactly what they want.

19:17.139 --> 19:18.571
And that would make them feel good.

19:18.573 --> 19:20.507
And that's a bad thing?

19:22.210 --> 19:24.244
Making people happy is a bad thing?

19:24.246 --> 19:28.148
I don't care about
what other people want.

19:28.150 --> 19:30.817
I care about what you want,
what you feel.

19:30.819 --> 19:33.253
Because the one person
getting lost in all of this

19:33.255 --> 19:35.155
is you.

19:35.157 --> 19:37.724
The real you is in there, Molly.

19:37.726 --> 19:39.292
You just need to find her.

19:41.363 --> 19:44.998
Would you be willing to try
something a little different?

19:48.670 --> 19:51.437
<i>Your assignment may
seem a little morbid,</i>

19:51.439 --> 19:54.774
<i>but I promise, it'll be very helpful.</i>

19:54.776 --> 19:57.277
<i>I want you to imagine your own funeral.</i>

19:57.828 --> 19:58.745
<i>Who would be there,</i>

19:58.747 --> 20:00.880
<i>and what would they say about you?</i>

20:00.882 --> 20:03.216
<i>[atmospheric music]</i>

20:03.218 --> 20:05.018
[door opens]

20:05.020 --> 20:08.021
<i>[faint organ music]</i>

20:08.023 --> 20:15.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:17.032 --> 20:18.298
[door opens]

20:18.300 --> 20:20.533
Ow. Hey, come on, watch it.

20:20.535 --> 20:24.103
You try seeing anything
in this stupid veil.

20:24.105 --> 20:26.105
Guys, hold on. Is this the right place?

20:26.107 --> 20:28.208
- Nobody's here.
- Must be the right place.

20:28.210 --> 20:29.742
After you, Morticia.

20:29.744 --> 20:33.713
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:33.715 --> 20:35.448
Honestly, does Maddie think

20:35.450 --> 20:36.983
that I would actually wear this?

20:36.985 --> 20:39.052
I look like Melania
Trump at the Vatican.

20:39.054 --> 20:41.087
I guess she wanted to see
my pecs one last time.

20:41.089 --> 20:42.589
I can barely breathe in this thing.

20:42.591 --> 20:43.623
What's she got you in?

20:43.625 --> 20:45.458
This is my wedding suit.

20:45.460 --> 20:46.960
- Huh.
- Oof.

20:46.962 --> 20:49.362
That is some messed up shit.

20:51.566 --> 20:53.299
Someone please say something.

20:53.301 --> 20:55.235
Okay, I think one of us
should say something.

20:55.237 --> 20:56.636
I'm wearing this dumbass veil.

20:56.638 --> 20:57.637
That's all she's getting out of me.

20:57.639 --> 20:59.606
Fine, I'll do it.

20:59.608 --> 21:05.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:05.814 --> 21:07.614
Dearly beloved...

21:07.616 --> 21:09.616
"Beloved." That's, uh... [laughs]

21:09.618 --> 21:12.685
That's funny. Um...

21:12.687 --> 21:16.756
I'm here because I wanted
to be someone's beloved.

21:19.127 --> 21:21.995
And for a few happy months,

21:21.997 --> 21:23.596
I thought I was.

21:23.598 --> 21:25.498
Here's the really crazy thing.

21:25.500 --> 21:28.301
I actually feel grateful that
Maddie Jonson happened to me.

21:28.303 --> 21:32.038
She taught me something
incredibly important:

21:32.040 --> 21:34.674
that I was capable of real love.

21:34.676 --> 21:36.142
[sniffs]

21:36.144 --> 21:38.211
- Are you crying?
- Shut up.

21:38.213 --> 21:39.412
Here's what else I know.

21:39.414 --> 21:42.148
I will find love again.

21:42.150 --> 21:43.816
Like you told me.

21:43.818 --> 21:45.551
Because it's worth the risk

21:45.553 --> 21:46.986
and the pain.

21:46.988 --> 21:48.655
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:48.657 --> 21:50.657
That's what's so...

21:50.659 --> 21:52.392
sad about today.

21:52.394 --> 21:54.027
[footsteps echoing]

21:54.029 --> 21:56.663
Did you die without knowing true love?

21:56.665 --> 22:01.301
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:01.303 --> 22:05.338
Without ever having
someone to call beloved?

22:05.340 --> 22:07.140
That is such a sad way to die.

22:07.142 --> 22:12.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:12.213 --> 22:13.880
Ah, it's Ezra.

22:15.817 --> 22:16.849
No!

22:16.851 --> 22:18.051
[gunshot]

22:21.523 --> 22:23.189
- Molly?
- [gasps]

22:25.226 --> 22:27.493
Um, inner light workshop

22:27.495 --> 22:28.761
is starting in about five minutes.

22:28.763 --> 22:30.697
- You want to come with me?
- Yeah.

22:30.699 --> 22:32.732
You okay?

22:32.734 --> 22:34.267
[exhales shakily]

22:34.269 --> 22:35.802
No.

22:39.374 --> 22:41.074
<i>You remember that time, Sal?</i>

22:41.076 --> 22:43.609
It was after that Reno job.

22:43.611 --> 22:45.411
I'm in a tux. You're in a ball gown.

22:45.413 --> 22:47.080
We drove through the night,
and we finally

22:47.082 --> 22:50.083
pulled into that rinky-dink gas station.

22:50.085 --> 22:52.318
I was coming back from
the cashier when I...

22:52.320 --> 22:56.055
I spied you talking to that little girl.

22:56.057 --> 22:57.857
She saw you in that gown,
and I heard her ask you,

22:57.859 --> 22:59.425
"Excuse me.

22:59.427 --> 23:01.427
"Are you the queen?"

23:01.429 --> 23:02.762
[chuckles]

23:02.764 --> 23:03.863
And you looked her right in the eye,

23:03.865 --> 23:05.398
and you said, "Yes.

23:05.400 --> 23:08.468
"Yes, young lady. I am."

23:08.470 --> 23:10.136
[chuckles]

23:10.138 --> 23:12.071
I got to tell you, Sal,

23:12.073 --> 23:13.639
we might have taken a
few things from people

23:13.641 --> 23:16.075
along the way, you know, but...

23:16.077 --> 23:17.744
I have to believe that little girl,

23:17.746 --> 23:20.446
'cause she'd never seen
anything that beautiful

23:20.448 --> 23:21.781
in her whole life.

23:25.620 --> 23:27.253
You gave her something.

23:29.657 --> 23:31.657
Take a left here.

23:31.659 --> 23:34.660
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:34.662 --> 23:39.799
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:39.801 --> 23:43.136
At least now I know where we are.

23:43.138 --> 23:44.337
What's the play, Sal?

23:44.339 --> 23:45.438
Car's gone.

23:45.440 --> 23:47.373
Looks like they're out.

23:47.375 --> 23:54.447
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:04.359 --> 24:07.059
God damn it, Sal, say something.

24:10.098 --> 24:12.365
You think I'm the one who betrayed you?

24:12.367 --> 24:14.200
You're the one who screwed me.

24:14.202 --> 24:16.536
You found Heller's money,
and you ran, and don't tell me

24:16.538 --> 24:18.471
you were gonna send me
a postcard from Panama.

24:18.473 --> 24:21.374
"Maxie, come join me." No.

24:21.376 --> 24:23.643
No, you were getting out for you.

24:23.645 --> 24:25.878
Well, maybe I should just blow
your brains out right now,

24:25.880 --> 24:26.879
be done with it.

24:26.881 --> 24:28.581
You're not a killer, Sal.

24:30.552 --> 24:32.185
Try me, Maxie.

24:32.187 --> 24:33.820
Just try me.

24:35.190 --> 24:36.823
[bell tolling]

24:36.825 --> 24:38.791
[people speaking Spanish]

24:38.793 --> 24:40.526
All right, all right,
here we go, here we go.

24:40.528 --> 24:42.295
You're on his left.
Go to the left, go to the left!

24:42.297 --> 24:44.063
No, no, no, no! Fire.
Fire, fire, fire, fire, fire!

24:44.065 --> 24:45.832
Here we go. Here we go, baby, come on.

24:45.834 --> 24:47.567
No!

24:47.569 --> 24:50.136
[speaking Spanish]

24:50.138 --> 24:52.805
<i>Lo siento, lo siento.</i>

24:52.807 --> 24:54.507
[sighs]

24:55.182 --> 24:56.308
_

24:58.680 --> 25:00.713
Oh, shit.

25:04.419 --> 25:06.385
[sighs]

25:14.128 --> 25:15.628
Eddie?

25:22.604 --> 25:24.904
[speaking Spanish]

25:24.906 --> 25:26.205
[inhales sharply]

25:28.443 --> 25:30.243
Morning.

25:30.245 --> 25:31.577
Looking for this?

25:31.579 --> 25:32.912
That's not funny.

25:32.914 --> 25:34.914
[laughs]

25:34.916 --> 25:36.449
What bothered you more,

25:36.451 --> 25:38.885
that I took the money,
or that I was gone?

25:38.887 --> 25:41.654
- Obviously the money.
- Obviously.

25:41.656 --> 25:44.323
[chuckles] You know,
you're a bad liar for a con artist.

25:44.325 --> 25:45.958
- I'm the best liar.
- Other than me.

25:45.960 --> 25:49.762
- Bullshit, baby dog eyes.
- All right.

25:49.764 --> 25:51.430
You say something to me.

25:51.432 --> 25:52.965
I'll tell you if you're lying.

25:52.967 --> 25:55.935
Then I'll say something to you,

25:55.937 --> 25:58.771
and we'll see who's better at this.

25:58.773 --> 26:00.606
You're gonna lose.

26:00.608 --> 26:02.808
We'll see.

26:02.810 --> 26:04.544
[clears throat]

26:04.546 --> 26:07.413
If you ever really steal from me,

26:07.415 --> 26:09.048
I will track you down,

26:09.050 --> 26:12.718
I will find you,
and I will make you pay.

26:12.720 --> 26:13.986
True.

26:13.988 --> 26:15.321
And terrifying.

26:15.811 --> 26:18.724
- Right? Your turn.
- All right.

26:18.726 --> 26:20.826
I don't give a shit about the money.

26:20.828 --> 26:22.795
Ever since I met you,

26:22.797 --> 26:24.330
I've been thinking of
ways to stay in Mexico

26:24.332 --> 26:26.098
just so I can be with you.

26:28.670 --> 26:30.403
Am I lying?

26:34.342 --> 26:36.809
[pounding at door]

26:38.580 --> 26:40.379
[pounding continues]

26:43.552 --> 26:44.517
What the hell?

26:44.519 --> 26:46.586
It's okay.

26:46.588 --> 26:49.055
Dude, oh, my God,
I just banged on, like, 17 doors.

26:49.057 --> 26:50.089
What the hell are you doing here?

26:50.091 --> 26:51.591
How'd you find me?

26:51.593 --> 26:52.592
We followed you here a few nights ago.

26:52.594 --> 26:53.793
- What?
- Eddie?

26:53.795 --> 26:55.328
It's okay. He's a friend of mine.

26:55.330 --> 26:56.629
We have a situation.
I was using your account

26:56.631 --> 26:57.997
to play "Knights of Meridia."

26:57.999 --> 26:59.432
You got a message while I was playing.

26:59.434 --> 27:02.268
What was the message?

27:02.270 --> 27:04.342
- I'm sorry, she's got to go.
- I'm not going anywhere.

27:04.377 --> 27:06.339
- Who the f... do you think you are?
- I'm the guy who knows

27:06.341 --> 27:07.373
that his real name is Ezra,

27:07.375 --> 27:08.641
- not Eddie.
- What?

27:08.643 --> 27:10.376
Yeah, my real name is... is Ezra.

27:10.378 --> 27:12.478
And there's probably a whole
lot of other serious shit

27:12.480 --> 27:14.647
that you don't know about him,
so I suggest

27:14.649 --> 27:16.716
you leave while you can, <i>comprende?</i>

27:16.718 --> 27:19.118
- Is that true?
- Um...

27:19.120 --> 27:20.453
[stammers] Which part?

27:23.024 --> 27:24.824
Okay, look, there are some things
I haven't told you,

27:24.826 --> 27:26.158
but for really good reasons, okay?

27:26.160 --> 27:27.393
You are pathetic.

27:27.395 --> 27:29.295
[mutters in Spanish]

27:29.297 --> 27:30.730
Hi.

27:30.732 --> 27:33.399
What the hell do you think you're doing?

27:33.401 --> 27:35.835
Ezra! You have to call your parents.

27:35.837 --> 27:37.536
Right now.

27:39.007 --> 27:42.642
<i>[line beeping]</i>

27:42.644 --> 27:44.377
Hello? Dad?

27:44.379 --> 27:47.146
Hey, kid,
it's your old friend Mr. Ellis.

27:48.916 --> 27:50.216
<i>Remember me?</i>

27:50.218 --> 27:52.652
Look, Mom and Dad are fine for now,

27:52.654 --> 27:54.754
but, uh...

27:54.756 --> 27:56.856
it's time for you to come home.

27:56.858 --> 27:58.557
We need to talk.

28:06.477 --> 28:11.594
_

28:12.856 --> 28:14.599
_

28:15.183 --> 28:16.797
_

28:17.283 --> 28:18.400
_

28:18.401 --> 28:19.401
_

28:19.627 --> 28:21.113
_

28:22.467 --> 28:23.920
_

28:25.088 --> 28:25.826
_

28:25.879 --> 28:27.279
Hey, I need to talk to Herman.

28:27.281 --> 28:28.780
I'm in the middle of something.

28:28.782 --> 28:30.282
Well, do you know where he is or not?

28:30.284 --> 28:31.850
Oh, now you seem to be
interested in our plans?

28:31.852 --> 28:33.719
- 'Cause you've been busy...
- Damn it, Jules.

28:33.721 --> 28:35.254
Tell me where he is.

28:39.293 --> 28:41.660
Upstairs. The room
next to the upside-down flag.

28:46.634 --> 28:48.800
What's going on?

28:48.802 --> 28:51.737
It's time to go back to the States.

28:51.739 --> 28:53.505
Now.

28:54.808 --> 28:55.941
<i>No, I get it. I get it.</i>

28:55.943 --> 28:57.542
You're... you're... you're in a hurry.

28:57.544 --> 28:58.810
Right.

28:58.812 --> 29:00.212
- It's very American.
- But...

29:00.214 --> 29:02.681
But... take a look around here, baby.

29:02.683 --> 29:04.883
[chuckles] Does this look
like a drive-through?

29:04.885 --> 29:07.586
You know,
you just got to trust the process.

29:07.588 --> 29:09.154
But... but what does that mean?

29:09.156 --> 29:10.922
It means you're gonna get your passports

29:10.924 --> 29:13.025
next week, just like I promised you.

29:13.027 --> 29:15.360
Fine. I'll figure out
another way to get across.

29:15.362 --> 29:16.528
No, hey, hey, hey!

29:16.530 --> 29:18.230
We still have a deal here,

29:18.232 --> 29:20.532
and I'm on the hook for
the cost of the passports,

29:20.534 --> 29:22.000
so you guys still owe me money.

29:22.002 --> 29:23.168
All right, man, chill out.

29:23.170 --> 29:24.503
Don't tell me to chill out.

29:24.505 --> 29:27.439
No, not around here!

29:27.441 --> 29:34.446
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:39.853 --> 29:41.520
[phone buzzes]

29:45.926 --> 29:47.859
Oh, shit.

29:47.861 --> 29:50.929
Shit. Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit.

29:50.931 --> 29:54.700
[children laughing]

29:54.702 --> 29:57.102
- There they are.
- Daddy!

29:57.104 --> 29:58.870
How's my birthday boy and girl?

29:58.872 --> 30:00.539
- Good.
- Yeah, you having fun?

30:00.541 --> 30:02.441
- Yeah.
- Good, good. Go have fun.

30:06.947 --> 30:08.380
[sighs]

30:11.585 --> 30:13.251
That's not an excuse, Patrick.

30:13.253 --> 30:14.953
Everybody's got a demanding job.

30:14.955 --> 30:16.621
Hey, I'm here, aren't I?

30:16.623 --> 30:18.957
I mean, a little late, but I'm here.

30:18.959 --> 30:19.991
Hey, can I help with anything?

30:19.993 --> 30:21.727
Oh, no, I'm...

30:21.729 --> 30:23.128
I think we got it, Leslie.

30:23.130 --> 30:24.796
Have you met my ex-husband?

30:24.798 --> 30:26.665
Hi, Leslie. Just moved next door.

30:26.667 --> 30:28.400
Patrick. Pleasure.
Where'd you move from?

30:28.402 --> 30:30.001
Ohio, a town called Fairfield,

30:30.003 --> 30:31.470
just outside Cincinnati.

30:31.472 --> 30:33.672
Oh, well, nice.
Welcome to the neighborhood.

30:33.674 --> 30:35.507
[exhales] Well.

30:35.509 --> 30:37.776
Okay. Let's go.

30:38.346 --> 30:41.113
<i>A town called Fairfield,
just outside Cincinnati.</i>

30:41.115 --> 30:43.915
We were originally from Cincinnati,
but we moved to Pottsville.

30:51.859 --> 30:53.325
Patrick.

30:53.427 --> 30:54.926
Patrick.

30:54.928 --> 30:57.696
I-I just realized
something really important.

30:57.698 --> 30:59.431
Me too.

30:59.433 --> 31:01.099
Listen, Patrick, if you still want

31:01.101 --> 31:05.303
to be part of the life of
this family in any way,

31:05.305 --> 31:06.972
you need to make a choice.

31:15.115 --> 31:16.648
<i>You realize you have a long way to go</i>

31:16.650 --> 31:18.016
to earn back your place,

31:18.018 --> 31:19.651
and asking for time off?

31:19.653 --> 31:20.819
Probably not the smartest thing.

31:20.821 --> 31:21.820
Yeah.

31:21.822 --> 31:23.822
Yeah, I know, but I...

31:23.824 --> 31:25.857
I really need to reconnect

31:25.859 --> 31:29.127
with my wife, my kids.

31:29.129 --> 31:30.962
Or I'm probably gonna lose them.

31:30.964 --> 31:34.466
Well, you're not exactly
critical to the team.

31:34.468 --> 31:35.567
I'll give you two weeks.

31:35.569 --> 31:36.935
Unpaid.

31:49.049 --> 31:50.282
Hey.

31:52.920 --> 31:54.553
Can... can I sit down?

32:04.097 --> 32:06.431
You win. You are the best liar.

32:06.433 --> 32:09.968
[sighs] I didn't lie about anything.

32:09.970 --> 32:11.903
Except my name.

32:11.905 --> 32:14.840
There is the lie of the
things you don't say.

32:14.842 --> 32:17.209
Who was that man?

32:17.211 --> 32:18.677
One of my friends.

32:20.747 --> 32:23.181
[sighs] One of my... partners.

32:23.183 --> 32:24.783
It's, uh...

32:24.785 --> 32:26.251
it's a long story.

32:26.253 --> 32:27.352
It always is.

32:27.354 --> 32:29.955
Please listen.

32:29.957 --> 32:31.857
My family is in danger.

32:31.859 --> 32:34.192
I have to get back to the
States as soon as I can.

32:34.194 --> 32:35.694
Are you asking my permission?

32:35.696 --> 32:37.095
You have it.

32:37.097 --> 32:38.730
But if you need money
for a plane ticket,

32:38.732 --> 32:40.198
I can't help.

32:40.200 --> 32:41.299
I can't take a plane.

32:41.301 --> 32:42.501
I need...

32:44.404 --> 32:46.104
I need to sneak across the border.

32:46.106 --> 32:48.473
- Can you help me with that?
- Why should I?

32:48.475 --> 32:49.541
'Cause I have nowhere else to turn

32:49.543 --> 32:51.276
and no one else I can trust.

32:53.046 --> 32:54.779
And...

32:54.781 --> 32:56.681
because we fit.

33:07.928 --> 33:10.562
I need to hear this story.

33:10.564 --> 33:13.298
Of your family and why you're here.

33:13.300 --> 33:15.333
And then...

33:15.335 --> 33:16.635
maybe.

33:21.675 --> 33:25.243
So all three of you were married to her,

33:25.245 --> 33:26.745
and she took everything?

33:26.747 --> 33:28.647
- Yeah.
- And this ring, which is...

33:28.649 --> 33:31.316
- In Arizona.
- How much is it worth?

33:31.318 --> 33:33.051
At least a million dollars.

33:35.355 --> 33:37.188
And if you give it to the bad guys,

33:37.190 --> 33:38.523
then your family is free?

33:38.525 --> 33:39.824
No, I don't know what they want, okay?

33:39.826 --> 33:41.426
I just... I just have to get to them.

33:41.428 --> 33:44.095
[sighs]

33:44.097 --> 33:45.964
Okay.

33:45.966 --> 33:48.033
Yeah?

33:48.035 --> 33:51.002
I know people who know people.

33:51.004 --> 33:54.506
These are dangerous things,

33:54.508 --> 33:55.507
but I'll help you.

33:55.509 --> 33:57.509
- Really?
- Really.

33:57.511 --> 34:00.445
But I have two things to say.

34:00.447 --> 34:02.847
Okay, anything.

34:02.849 --> 34:04.883
One,

34:04.885 --> 34:06.184
my name is not Rosa.

34:06.186 --> 34:07.652
It's Sofia.

34:09.656 --> 34:12.791
And two, when you get it back,

34:12.793 --> 34:15.126
I get 10% of the ring.

34:15.128 --> 34:19.063
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:19.065 --> 34:21.333
Okay.

34:21.335 --> 34:22.967
Deal.

34:22.969 --> 34:25.402
Good.

34:25.405 --> 34:27.539
[chuckles]

34:37.780 --> 34:39.347
Well, that's time.

34:39.349 --> 34:42.083
Molly, what's the point of
you sitting here with me

34:42.085 --> 34:43.650
if you won't talk?

34:45.455 --> 34:47.755
Isn't silence better than lying?

34:47.757 --> 34:49.157
It is,

34:49.159 --> 34:50.358
but there are a lot of other places

34:50.360 --> 34:52.360
where you can practice silence.

34:52.362 --> 34:54.362
Instead you choose to sit here with me.

34:54.364 --> 34:57.365
Why? I think it's pretty simple.

34:57.367 --> 35:00.702
I think it's because you
want to tell me the truth.

35:00.704 --> 35:02.637
So when you're ready to do that,

35:02.639 --> 35:04.005
let me know.

35:04.007 --> 35:06.607
Until then, our sessions are over.

35:06.609 --> 35:08.643
Wait, you're kicking me out of therapy?

35:08.645 --> 35:10.011
Molly, you're not in therapy.

35:10.013 --> 35:12.880
You haven't been here this whole time.

35:12.882 --> 35:14.248
Good luck.

35:16.786 --> 35:17.852
I don't understand.

35:17.854 --> 35:19.387
Who's Sofia?

35:19.389 --> 35:20.888
You met her at the hotel. The one...

35:20.890 --> 35:22.190
Yeah, the one he didn't tell us about.

35:22.192 --> 35:23.624
His secret lover.

35:23.626 --> 35:26.194
Okay, then why
were you calling her Rosa?

35:26.196 --> 35:27.495
That was a nickname.

35:27.497 --> 35:28.730
[scoffs] He doesn't even know

35:28.732 --> 35:30.565
- her real name.
- Yeah, I do.

35:30.567 --> 35:32.533
It's Sofia,
and she has connections to a coyote.

35:32.535 --> 35:34.736
That's the point.
We get ourselves to the border.

35:34.738 --> 35:36.904
- The coyote smuggles us across.
- Absolutely not.

35:36.906 --> 35:38.539
I'm not shoving a bag of coke up my ass.

35:38.541 --> 35:39.607
Not for you, not for anyone.

35:39.609 --> 35:41.008
That's a mule, Richard,

35:41.010 --> 35:42.243
not a <i>coyote.</i>

35:42.245 --> 35:43.578
I'm sorry, a <i>"coyote."</i>

35:43.580 --> 35:44.879
No. Not happening.

35:44.881 --> 35:46.914
- Wack plan.
- You got a better idea?

35:46.916 --> 35:49.550
This girl who you've been
secretly banging on the side,

35:49.552 --> 35:51.152
whose real name you may or may not know

35:51.154 --> 35:52.687
suddenly wants to just bail us out?

35:52.689 --> 35:54.255
That doesn't seem a
little sketch to you?

35:54.257 --> 35:55.590
Yeah, well,
in case you haven't noticed, Richard,

35:55.592 --> 35:57.892
we don't have a lot
of options right now.

35:57.894 --> 35:59.327
Could you chime in here, please?

35:59.329 --> 36:02.213
- I agree with Richard.
- Hoo! Hot damn.

36:02.248 --> 36:03.507
Yo, write that down in your little book.

36:03.542 --> 36:04.265
- I don't believe this.
- How do we know

36:04.267 --> 36:05.399
we can trust her, whatever her name is?

36:05.401 --> 36:08.069
Yeah, man, since when do you
get to make all the decisions?

36:08.071 --> 36:09.337
Yeah, how about when your
family's taken hostage,

36:09.339 --> 36:10.571
you can be in charge.

36:10.573 --> 36:12.106
You want to figure out your own way?

36:12.108 --> 36:14.408
I don't give a shit.
This is what I'm doing.

36:14.410 --> 36:15.409
You in or out?

36:17.013 --> 36:19.347
How much does this <i>coyote</i> cost?

36:19.349 --> 36:21.115
An extra ten grand.

36:21.117 --> 36:23.451
- By tomorrow.
- [scoffs]

36:23.453 --> 36:24.585
Well, then, we're screwed, man.

36:24.587 --> 36:25.953
That's impossible, all right,

36:25.955 --> 36:28.122
even for you, Mr. Sticky Fingers.

36:28.124 --> 36:30.258
It's not impossible.

36:32.695 --> 36:35.730
[speaking Spanish]

36:39.736 --> 36:41.469
- Well, I sent the request.
- Yeah?

36:41.471 --> 36:43.538
$10,000 to be wired here tomorrow.

36:43.540 --> 36:45.273
You sure it'll come through?

36:45.275 --> 36:46.941
Let's just say my family
takes a certain delight

36:46.943 --> 36:48.376
in rescuing me.

36:48.378 --> 36:49.844
All right.

36:49.846 --> 36:51.579
You understand the only
reason I'm doing this

36:51.581 --> 36:53.948
is because it's an emergency
and lives are at stake?

36:56.419 --> 36:57.852
And because it's you.

36:58.922 --> 37:01.289
Yeah, I know.

37:01.291 --> 37:02.356
[horn honks twice]

37:05.328 --> 37:07.962
You sure you trust her?

37:07.964 --> 37:09.497
Be careful, Ez.

37:09.499 --> 37:11.032
I will.

37:15.672 --> 37:17.939
<i>- Hola.
- Hola, guapo.</i>

37:19.175 --> 37:21.342
I hope everybody likes tuna fish.

37:21.344 --> 37:22.977
It's all I had.

37:22.979 --> 37:24.478
Tuna's great.

37:24.480 --> 37:27.148
- Hungry, Sal?
- You eat first.

37:27.150 --> 37:29.083
- [clanking, rumbling]
- What the hell is that?

37:29.085 --> 37:30.484
- The garage.
- Oh, shit.

37:30.486 --> 37:32.854
I told Josh he could
borrow the Weedwacker.

37:32.856 --> 37:34.155
[door opens]

37:41.664 --> 37:43.364
- Hi, guys.
- Hi, sweetie.

37:43.366 --> 37:45.633
I see you got the Weedwacker.

37:45.635 --> 37:47.768
Yeah, I just wanted to see if
Dad had extra gas for this...

37:47.770 --> 37:49.136
Everything okay?

37:49.138 --> 37:50.204
We're fine, son.

37:50.206 --> 37:51.305
We're not fine.

37:51.307 --> 37:52.506
We're, um, fighting.

37:52.508 --> 37:54.041
Oh, God, you're fighting?

37:54.043 --> 37:55.710
- Mind your own business.
- Just a little dispute.

37:55.712 --> 37:57.278
Okay, but like,
you're not getting divorced, right?

37:57.280 --> 37:58.880
- Josh, get out.
- Don't be ridiculous.

37:58.882 --> 38:00.681
- Fine.
- And keep the Weedwacker

38:00.683 --> 38:02.183
for as long as you need.

38:02.185 --> 38:04.018
Okay.

38:05.321 --> 38:09.223
<i>[tense music]</i>

38:09.225 --> 38:11.125
[mouthing words]

38:12.295 --> 38:13.794
I'll bring it back next week.

38:13.796 --> 38:15.029
Bye.

38:15.031 --> 38:16.964
Close the garage door, sweetie.

38:16.966 --> 38:20.001
[clanking, rumbling]

38:24.507 --> 38:25.506
[whirring]

38:25.508 --> 38:26.874
[shouts]

38:26.876 --> 38:27.875
Josh!

38:28.398 --> 38:30.311
- Shit!
- Stop!

38:30.313 --> 38:32.513
Looks like we got
ourselves a little reunion.

38:37.359 --> 38:40.786
<i>♪ I would climb the highest mountain ♪</i>

38:40.788 --> 38:43.989
<i>♪ Cross the deepest river ♪</i>

38:43.991 --> 38:48.193
<i>♪ Just to be next to you ♪</i>

38:48.195 --> 38:49.695
[lock beeps]

38:49.697 --> 38:53.465
<i>♪ Put me to the test ♪</i>

38:53.467 --> 38:55.701
<i>♪ Test my faithfulness ♪</i>

38:55.703 --> 38:57.369
Hello, Agent Cook.

38:57.371 --> 38:58.971
[laughs]

38:58.973 --> 39:00.305
You got to be shitting me.

39:00.307 --> 39:02.307
How's retirement treating you?

39:02.309 --> 39:03.542
Having fun?

39:03.544 --> 39:05.544
Pauline! Who's at the door?

39:05.546 --> 39:09.348
None of your damn business, Jerry.

39:09.350 --> 39:12.084
Does it look like I'm having fun?

39:12.086 --> 39:13.819
Let's talk.

39:13.821 --> 39:15.454
If you came here to apologize,

39:15.456 --> 39:17.990
I hope you brought me
more than funeral flowers.

39:17.992 --> 39:21.493
I think I got something better
than an apology for you.

39:21.495 --> 39:24.763
I think I have a way
to find Maddie Jonson.

39:24.765 --> 39:27.432
- And I need a partner.
- [laughs]

39:27.434 --> 39:28.867
That's why you came here?

39:28.869 --> 39:30.636
Patrick, it's over.

39:30.638 --> 39:32.604
We got played. I got put out to pasture.

39:32.606 --> 39:34.273
Go eat your humble pie.

39:34.275 --> 39:36.508
Agent Cook, I need your help.

39:36.510 --> 39:39.444
Okay, I know it galls you.

39:39.446 --> 39:41.280
Just as much as it galls me.

39:41.282 --> 39:43.882
What galls me is,
I let you talk me into something

39:43.884 --> 39:46.251
I knew was going pear-shaped.

39:46.253 --> 39:48.754
Colleen! Is this lunch meat still good?

39:48.756 --> 39:52.024
Smell it, Jerry.
If it smells bad, don't eat it.

39:52.026 --> 39:55.894
Listen, we never knew where
Maddie was really from.

39:55.896 --> 40:00.365
But I think it's Pottsville,
Pennsylvania.

40:00.367 --> 40:01.767
Come with me.

40:01.769 --> 40:05.304
I would really like your help.

40:05.306 --> 40:06.305
If I do this...

40:06.307 --> 40:08.573
<i>if</i> I do this,

40:08.575 --> 40:10.242
I have one condition.

40:10.244 --> 40:12.778
Name it.

40:12.780 --> 40:16.915
After we find Maddie Jonson,
we take down the Doctor too.

40:16.917 --> 40:19.751
Now that I like.

40:19.753 --> 40:21.853
- Deal.
- Deal.

40:22.856 --> 40:25.290
I don't understand. What happened?

40:25.292 --> 40:28.126
Nothing. I can't take this place.

40:28.128 --> 40:30.262
I can't deal with it, I can't afford it,

40:30.264 --> 40:31.763
and I just... I got to go.

40:31.765 --> 40:33.632
But, Molly,
you were doing so great yesterday.

40:33.634 --> 40:36.335
Your share in group about your sister...

40:36.337 --> 40:37.903
I was really moved by that.

40:37.905 --> 40:39.304
Linda, I lied to you.

40:39.306 --> 40:41.073
Okay? I don't even have a sister.

40:41.075 --> 40:43.275
I just said that stuff so you'd like me.

40:43.277 --> 40:44.876
How messed up is that?

40:44.878 --> 40:47.479
You know what? That's a breakthrough.

40:47.481 --> 40:50.015
- [laughs]
- See? No, you can't leave.

40:50.017 --> 40:52.818
You're just getting started.

40:52.820 --> 40:55.454
Look, truth be told,
I don't really believe in all this,

40:55.456 --> 40:59.124
you know,
"the universe has a plan for you" BS.

40:59.126 --> 41:02.427
But I do believe in what's
right in front of you,

41:02.429 --> 41:07.466
and you are here right now for a reason.

41:07.468 --> 41:09.267
Linda, what's right in front of me

41:09.269 --> 41:11.603
is a bill I can't afford, okay?

41:11.605 --> 41:12.604
I'm sorry, I got to go.

41:12.606 --> 41:13.839
What if you had a friend

41:13.841 --> 41:15.574
that could help you with that bill?

41:18.145 --> 41:19.644
Take care of yourself, okay?

41:22.082 --> 41:24.049
<i>♪ Daydream ♪</i>

41:24.051 --> 41:27.619
<i>♪ I fell asleep amid the flowers ♪</i>

41:27.621 --> 41:31.523
<i>♪ For a couple of hours ♪</i>

41:31.525 --> 41:33.892
<i>♪ On a beautiful day ♪</i>

41:33.894 --> 41:36.294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:36.296 --> 41:38.497
<i>♪ Daydream ♪</i>

41:38.499 --> 41:42.000
<i>♪ I dream of you amid the flowers ♪</i>

41:42.002 --> 41:45.303
<i>♪ For a couple of hours ♪</i>

41:45.305 --> 41:48.140
<i>♪ Such a beautiful day ♪</i>

41:48.142 --> 41:50.475
[panting]

41:50.477 --> 41:52.878
[children laughing]

41:52.880 --> 41:54.679
[whistle blows]

41:54.681 --> 41:57.716
<i>[heart thumping]</i>

42:00.654 --> 42:03.088
[footsteps approaching]

42:03.090 --> 42:05.791
[knocking]

42:12.866 --> 42:15.700
What I tell you in here...

42:16.937 --> 42:19.738
By law, what are you required to report?

42:22.276 --> 42:25.610
Well, if I believe you're a
danger to yourself or others,

42:25.612 --> 42:29.514
if you plan on committing
a crime in the future,

42:29.516 --> 42:31.516
or if there are children involved.

42:31.518 --> 42:33.051
Those I report.

42:33.053 --> 42:35.587
Anything else is between us.

42:35.589 --> 42:38.590
<i>[soft music]</i>

42:38.592 --> 42:42.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:42.429 --> 42:44.596
I'd like to make an appointment.

42:46.567 --> 42:49.601
I'm ready to tell you the truth...

42:49.603 --> 42:50.669
about everything.

